2002-01-01|2002-12-30.description: Hoichi's taken a hit -- a Riofald kinetic round straight to the head of Exaxxion. The robot's okay, but there's only one problem. Hoichi isn't breathing! If the dude could wake up, he might notice that the humans are amassing forces all around his robot's head and feet. But no, he's off in la-la land, dreaming of days gone by... Meanwhile, Ambassador Shes'ka has problems of his own. His commanding officer on home world is demanding an explanation of the mysterious XXX alert, and he doesn't believe the ambassador's story that it was a false alarm. Drama and destruction abound as the curtain falls on Cannon God Exaxxion Stage 1.

Astro remains stranded in the 20th century, but he's certainly not laying about! Astro must save the Earth from a voracious Martian fungus -- and save the intelligent organism from the hydrogen bomb -- all the while having to begin the fight for robot's rights and to keep robots from fighting each other!

Story Titles

  • Living Mold from Outer Space
  • A Declaration of Robot Rights
  • Astro Goes to Elementary School
  • Gone with the Snow
  • The Faceless Robot

2002-01-01|2002-12-30.description: Thorgal's son, Jolan, has grown up to be a strong and inquisitive child while the three of them live on a deserted island. His parents are puzzled by the strange symbols he keeps drawing of which he can't tell their meaning. In his mind find friendship with a boy of his age that seems to come out of the nowhere. The child seems to be lost and afraid of adults. Also because he is a mute he isn't able to answer any questions regarding his mysterious and sudden presence.
